rComments: fun class and small size made for more interactive setting & hes very invested in success of students. lectures can be hard to follow, but differential equations is a disorganized subject, so just ask Qs and go to office hours. very helpful in office hours. take good notes!!! tests are based off lecture examples. good prof overall highly recommend

Excellent professor for one of the hardest classes offered by math dept. lectures go by fast and material is DENSE! If u want to survive, take notes & work thru proofs afterwards. Best in office hours; will talk u thru proofs; encouraging/thoughtful. got A- but didnt come easy; learned more from this guy than any other prof, highly recommend.

I loved this professor! Yes, he has an accent, but what Math teacher doesn't? He goes over the material VERY thoroughly, and while he covers everything you need to know for 23B, he really only tests on the "easy" half of the course. I got C's on all three tests in his class, did all the homework, and got an A. Awesome curve, love this guy!

He means well, his accent is difficult but after a couple of weeks you know what he is trying to say, i got a 64 on the midterm and a 72 on the final and ended the class with a B so he curves quite a lot. Overall do your homework and the tests should be fine, go over midterm b/c the same exact questions on the midterm were on the final

Qing is very hard to understand although he tried to explain concepts clearly. Lecture wasn't necessary because he posted his notes online. Tests were straightforward and were pretty basic. I can't say I would reccommend him as a teacher because I only learned through the crappy textbook.
He is a very kind professor and he really enjoys helping his students. His class is generally simple and traditional in terms of work and the teachings. I really enjoyed being in his class.
Doesn't speak or write clearly. I gained almost nothing from attending class and ended up having to learn vector calculus from the book which sucks. AVOID HIM IF AT ALL POSSIBLE

Tries really hard to make sure students understand what is going on.  Will not get irritated when stopped because of a question.  Has an accent.  Goes over concepts more than over examples.  Tests were not conceptual and similar to homework problems.

I was pretty terrified to take Math 105 because I always heard how hard it was, and I knew nothing about Qing before I took the class. It ended up being an all around good experience. The class was interesting, Qing was very clear in lecture and sections helped. It is a hard class, but I got a B+ without really trying too hard.
lol Jie is one of the funniest math teachers I've had. really explains concepts clearly and does a great job with bringing difficult concepts into the open.
